data.chText: 产生预期结果的；有效的
data.enText: producing the result that is wanted or intended; producing a successful result

data.chText: 判处长期徒刑可对违法者起到强有力的威慑作用。
data.enText: Long prison sentences can be a very effective deterrent for offenders.

data.chText: 阿司匹林药片治疗方法简便，效果却非常显著。
data.enText: Aspirin is a simple but highly effective treatment.
drugs that are effective against cancer

data.chText: 我很欣赏她绘画作品中的色彩效果。
data.enText: I admire the effective use of colour in her paintings.
in reality, although not officially intended

data.chText: 虽未居其位却实际上是党的领导人
data.enText: the effective, if not the actual, leader of the party

data.chText: 他目前已有效地控制了这个国家。
data.enText: He has now taken effective control of the country.

data.chText: 这条路上新的限速规定自6月1日起生效。
data.enText: The new speed limit on this road becomes effective from 1 June.

data.chText: 检查安全系统的有效性
data.enText: to check the effectiveness of the security system

ex.chText: 政府采取了有效措施来降低物价。
ex.enText: The government took effective measures to reduce the price.

ex.chText: 双方会谈有效地解决了彼此间的纠纷。
ex.enText: The talks between both sides were effective in settling their disputes.

synonyms.bx: 指有效用的或能产生预期效果的。

ex.chText: 政府尚未找到应对失业的有效措施。
ex.enText: The government hasn't worked out the effectual measures to combat unemployment.

ex.chText: 奎宁是预防疟疾的有效药物。
ex.enText: Quinine is an effectual preventive for malaria.

synonyms.bx: 指产生希望或想要的结果的，只用于事物，如举措、药物、对策等。

ex.enText: The diesel engine is highly efficient.

synonyms.bx: 既可指人也可指事物，强调不浪费时间、金钱、能源等的。

example: a decline in the effective demand
confused increased equipment and expenditure with the quantity of effective work done
people who will do nothing unless they get something out of it for themselves are often highly effective persons..."-G.B.Sha
the efficient cause of the revolution
a warranty good for two years
the law is already in effect (or in force)

tr: producing or capable of producing an intended result or having a striking effect
example: an air-cooled motor was more effective than a witch's broomstick for rapid long-distance transportation"-LewisMumfor
his complaint proved to be effectual in bringing action

tr: works well as a means or remedy
example: a lotion that is effective in cases of prickly heat
the fort was held by about 100 effective soldiers

value.def: Something that is effective works well and produces the results that were intended.

example.ex: The project looks at how we could be more effective in encouraging students to enter teacher training...
example.tran: 该项目着眼于我们如何能够更加有效地鼓励学生参与教师培训。

example.ex: Simple antibiotics are effective against this organism...
example.tran: 一般的抗生素能够有效对抗这种微生物。
有效运转的公共交通系统

value.tran: 有效的;能产生预期效果的

example.ex: ...the team roles which you believe to be necessary for the team to function effectively...
example.tran: 你认为要使团队有效运作所必需的团队作用

example.ex: Services need to be more effectively organised than they are at present.
example.tran: 服务的管理应该比现在更加有效。

example.ex: ...the effectiveness of computers as an educational tool.
example.tran: 计算机作为教育工具的有效性

value.def: Effective means having a particular role or result in practice, though not officially or in theory.

example.ex: They have had effective control of the area since the security forces left.
example.tran: 自从安全部队撤离后，他们实际上控制了该地区。

example.ex: ...a restructuring that would have resulted in an effective increase on one of their most popular excursion fares.
example.tran: 原本会使他们最热门的一条短途旅游线路的费用出现实质性上涨的调整

value.def: When something such as a law or an agreement becomes effective, it begins officially to apply or be valid.

example.ex: The new rules will become effective in the next few days.
example.tran: 新规定将在几天后生效。

value.tran: （法律、协议等）生效的，起作用的

trans: 有成本效率的，节省成本有效果的，本轻利厚的
有效需求；有支付能力的需求
有效行动；有效的行动；有效作用量；结果的行动；有效作用
有效质量；有效質量；有效重量；等效质量；电子的有效质量
有效折射率；等效折射率；有效指标；有效指数
实际（有效）渗透率；有效透磁率，有效导磁率，有效磁导率
